<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta haemorrhoidalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis" status="comb. nov.">Calameuta haemorrhoidalis</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Gussakovskij, VV" editor="Stackelberg, AA" journalOrPublisher="Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscou, Leningrad 2 (1)" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 453" refId="B57" refString="Gussakovskij, VV, 1935. Insectes Hymenopteres, Chalastogastra 1. In: Stackelberg, AA, Ed., Faune de l'URSS. Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscou, Leningrad 2(1): 1 - 453" title="Insectes Hymenopteres, Chalastogastra 1." volumeTitle="Faune de l'URSS." year="1935">Gussakovskij (1935)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1946.tb00445.x" author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="89 - 108" refId="B9" refString="Benson, RB, 1946. Classification of the Cephidae (Hymenoptera Symphyta). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 96 (6): 89 - 108, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1946.tb00445.x" title="Classification of the Cephidae (Hymenoptera Symphyta)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1946.tb00445.x" volume="96" year="1946">Benson (1946)</bibRefCitation>
, and most subsequent authors.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Type material examined and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephus variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Cephus variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, 1886, hereby designated: ♀, id nr.017651 HNHM Hym.coll. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Calameuta variabilis (Mocsary, 1886). A. Lateral habitus and labels, lectotype ♀ Cephus variabilis Mocsary, 1886; B. Maxillary palp ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Palpomeres 5 and 6 (arrows); C. Thorax, dorsal ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Mesoscutum (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719516" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">5A</figureCitation>
); labels (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Calameuta variabilis (Mocsary, 1886). A. Lateral habitus and labels, lectotype ♀ Cephus variabilis Mocsary, 1886; B. Maxillary palp ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Palpomeres 5 and 6 (arrows); C. Thorax, dorsal ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Mesoscutum (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719516" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">5A</figureCitation>
). Type locality: Romania, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Herkulesfürdõ">Herkulesfuerdo</normalizedToken>
(HNHM). Paralectotypes (all HNHM): 5♂ and 2♀ also belong to the type series and have been labelled as paralectotypes: details of their sexes and localities were given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zombori, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="259 - 264" refId="B202" refString="Zombori, L, 1978. New Sawfly Species in the Hungarian Fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta), IV. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 70: 259 - 264" title="New Sawfly Species in the Hungarian Fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta), IV." volume="70" year="1978">Zombori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
. Note that the type series is heterogeneous, and contains specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta punctata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Calameuta punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Zombori noted the heterogeneity of the type series, but did not publish a lectotype designation, although the specimens were labelled by him as lectotype and paralectotypes. The types were found by Z. Vas in the HNHM, grouped as stated by Zombori. We do not follow 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Zombori’s">Zombori's</normalizedToken>
intention according to his labels, but designate the female from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Herculesfürdö">Herculesfuerdoe</normalizedToken>
(= Baile Herculane, Romania) (id nr. 017651 HNHM Hym. coll., labelled by Z. Vas) as lectotype (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Calameuta variabilis (Mocsary, 1886). A. Lateral habitus and labels, lectotype ♀ Cephus variabilis Mocsary, 1886; B. Maxillary palp ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Palpomeres 5 and 6 (arrows); C. Thorax, dorsal ♀ (DEI-GISHym 14072). Mesoscutum (arrow)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719516" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">5A</figureCitation>
). Thus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Mocsary" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Calameuta variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, 1886) comb. nov. can be used as a valid name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta haemorrhoidalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Calameuta haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Gussakovskij et auct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephus atripes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Cephus atripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1835 has sometimes been listed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e,g. by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" author="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 1064" refId="B173" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2010. World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa 2580 (1): 1 - 1064, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" title="World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" volume="2580" year="2010">Taeger et al. (2010</bibRefCitation>
, under 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta haemorrhoidalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Calameuta haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The type specimen, or specimens, is probably lost. The description is short, and does not state the sex of the described specimens(s). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" author="de Dalla Torre, CG" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B37" refString="de Dalla Torre, CG, 1894. Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[6] pp.+ pp. I-VIII +] 1-459. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" title="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[ 6] pp. + pp. I-VIII +] 1 - 459." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" year="1894">de Dalla Torre (1894)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. atripes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="atripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. atripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. pygmeus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pygmeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. pygmeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1767) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Genera Insectorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 27" refId="B98" refString="Konow, FW, 1905a. Hymenoptera. Fam. Lydidae. Genera Insectorum 27: 1 - 27" title="Hymenoptera. Fam. Lydidae." volume="27" year="1905 a">Konow (1905a)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. haemorrhoidalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The color pattern described by Stephens does not fit very well with either of these, in either sex, nor with any other known north-west European cephid species. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stephens’">Stephens'</normalizedToken>
name is best treated as a species inquirendae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Biology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Macek, J" journalOrPublisher="Academia, Praha" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B124" refString="Macek, J, Roller, L, Benes, K, Holy, K, Holusa, J, 2020. Blanokridli Ceske a Slovenske republiky II. Siropasi. Academia, Praha" title="Blanokridli Ceske a Slovenske republiky II. Siropasi." year="2020">Macek et al. (2020</bibRefCitation>
, under 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1896" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Calameuta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calameuta haemorrhoidalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhoidalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Calameuta haemorrhoidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) the host plants of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are various 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, including cereals such as rye (
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Secale" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Secale cereale" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cereale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Secale cereale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and wheat (
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Triticum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Triticum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Triticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). According to our personal experiences, adults occur in dry places, mostly on or near wild grasses. The taxon to which the name 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. variabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now applied has so far been found only in the West Palaearctic, and has an essentially Mediterranean distribution, summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gussakovskij, VV" editor="Stackelberg, AA" journalOrPublisher="Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscou, Leningrad 2 (1)" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 453" refId="B57" refString="Gussakovskij, VV, 1935. Insectes Hymenopteres, Chalastogastra 1. In: Stackelberg, AA, Ed., Faune de l'URSS. Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscou, Leningrad 2(1): 1 - 453" title="Insectes Hymenopteres, Chalastogastra 1." volumeTitle="Faune de l'URSS." year="1935">Gussakovskij (1935)</bibRefCitation>
as comprising southern Europe, Crimea, Caucasus, western Turkmenia (Kopet-Dagh) and Syria. In Central Europe, it reaches at least as far north as Hungary (
<bibRefCitation author="Zombori, L" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="259 - 264" refId="B202" refString="Zombori, L, 1978. New Sawfly Species in the Hungarian Fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta), IV. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 70: 259 - 264" title="New Sawfly Species in the Hungarian Fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta), IV." volume="70" year="1978">Zombori 1978</bibRefCitation>
), but specimens recorded from Austria and the Czech Republic (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="399 - 504" refId="B172" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2006. European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries. In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 399 - 504" title="European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">Taeger et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
) should be checked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
